content.description: Start low on good right hand side pull and left hand crimp. Slap up and left to a dishy sloper, and then gain the left arete. Work your way to the crimp seam that trends diagonally right. Follow this seam to the jug ledge. Then use some cool overhead press and mantle, or go huge to the jug at the lip. Either way, don't go right into the finish of Minute Made.
content.location: To the left of "The Art of Peer Pressure".

content.description: Sit start on sloping crimp rail. Compress your way up between good side pulls. Finish straight up.
content.location: This problem shares a start with "The Art of Peer Pressure" but goes right into a compression line.

content.description: Sit start on sloping crimp rail. Trend left into good holds followed by some crimps. Gain the jug ledge and finish the same as "Pressing Matters".
content.location: Same start hold as "Minute Made", but trend left and finish up "Pressing Matters".

content.description: This area holds some fun boulders that are on the taller end. Mainly vertical climbing on some of the better rock quality at Ely's. There is a listing for this area in the Duluth Urban Cragger, but no routes are listed. The routes on this page are some that I thought were fun, and may or may not have been climbed before. If you have any further information on this area, please let me know and I can put it on here.
